<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> Try It Yourself </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      :root {
         background: #78969D;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p> The <b>:root</b> CSS pseudo-class matches the root element of a tree representing the document. In HTML, <b>:root</b> represents the <b>&lt;html&gt;</b> element. </p>
   
   <h3> Example: </h3>
   <p> As an example, we have changed the document's background color. </p>
</body>
</html>